PIXELLAB IS COMMITTED TO YOUR PRIVACY
We value Your patronage and respect Your privacy rights. As part of the normal operation of Our services, We collect and, in some cases, may disclose information about You. We have created the following Privacy Policy to let You know what information We collect when You use Our Service, why We collect it, and how it is used. This Privacy Policy applies to all information that You provide to PixelLab Ltd. ("Us," "We," or "Our") and that We maintain electronically, whether You provide the information through Our Service located at
www.pixellabltd.com
(the "Website"), or via any applications created by PixelLab Ltd. ("Apps"), and information made available by users to each other through the PixelLab Ltd. Software (collectively, the "Service"). Additionally, this Privacy Policy applies to any Personal Information (defined below) obtained from Your use of the Service. This Privacy Policy does not apply to any information that You may provide to third parties; for example, other sites linked to this Website and Apps. You should contact such third parties directly to determine their respective privacy policies. This Privacy Policy is governed by Our Terms and Conditions. PixelLab Ltd. reserves the right to change this Privacy Policy at any time without notice. Please check the privacy policy regularly. If You do not expressly object to the validity of the new terms and conditions/privacy Policy via e-mail within this two (2) week period, then the newly revised Privacy Policy will be considered agreed upon. If You reject the newly revised Privacy Policy, then PixelLab Ltd. may terminate its relationship with You. If You believe We have not adhered to this Privacy Policy or if You have any other questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact Us at
support@pixellabltd.com
.
WHICH DATA ARE WE COLLECTING?
Data We are collecting are either provided by You or collected automatically.
Data You provide Us:
Data that You provide during registration
Data that You provide for the billing of goods and services requiring payment
Data We collect automatically:
Data about Your game progress
Data about Your device, such as device name and operating system
General location data
Data about Your use of the Service such as game-play data
Data we receive if you link a third party tool with the Service (such as Facebook or Google)
Furthermore We collect and store information in the log files of our servers which are automatically transferred to us by Your Internet browser (i.e. without us requesting this data). This data among others includes:
Browser type and version
Operating system
Device type
Referrer URL (the previously visited site)
IP address of the accessing computer
Cookies
Time of the server request
Data collected automatically cannot be assigned to certain individuals by us. We use it in a pseudonymous and/or anonymous form for analytic purposes and to tailor and improve our Service according to the needs of the user. This data will not be combined with other data sources.
We process and use data You provide Us for providing the game Service or create accounts and allow you to use our Service and for billing our Services as well as for advertising purposes. In individual cases, We shall commission related companies or other third parties to provide services. This particularly applies to the handling of payments via external service providers (PayPal, Global Collect, etc.) as well as to collection agencies in the case of late payments. These external companies are obligated to treat Your data confidentially and safely to the extent required in fulfilling their duties.
Data in our Apps are collected through third party services. For more information about their privacy policies and opt-out possibilities, please visit the links below.
